that before someone gets hurt.

03:11.708 --> 03:13.572
Come on, get to class.

03:13.607 --> 03:18.370
[dramatic music]
[kids chattering]

03:18.405 --> 03:20.200
Let's go, let's go.

03:20.234 --> 03:21.925
- Let's go.

03:21.960 --> 03:23.064
Move.

03:23.099 --> 03:25.895
[dramatic music]

03:53.923 --> 03:55.062
[bell ringing]

03:55.096 --> 03:55.890
- [Vice Principal]
Please send Becky Hooper

03:55.925 --> 03:57.133
to the front office.

03:57.167 --> 03:59.135
Her father's here
to pick her up.

03:59.169 --> 04:01.827
[dramatic music]

04:09.318 --> 04:10.388
- [Guard] On your feet.

04:10.422 --> 04:13.183
[dramatic music]

04:25.506 --> 04:26.300
- [Jeff] Hi, Chipmunk.

04:26.335 --> 04:27.163
[car beeping]

04:27.197 --> 04:29.959
[dramatic music]

04:46.631 --> 04:49.634
[suspenseful music]

05:18.352 --> 05:19.974
- [Driver] Good back there?

05:20.009 --> 05:20.975
- Yup.

05:21.010 --> 05:23.012
[suspenseful music]

05:23.046 --> 05:28.051
[metal clanking]
[suspenseful music]

05:34.368 --> 05:36.853
[eerie music]

05:38.096 --> 05:39.649
- [Dominick] Excuse me.

05:39.684 --> 05:41.064
- What's going on?

05:41.099 --> 05:41.824
- [Dominick] There's something
wrong with this gentleman.

05:41.858 --> 05:42.652
- Shit.

05:42.687 --> 05:43.481
- [Driver] What?

05:43.515 --> 05:44.344
- Pull over.

05:44.378 --> 05:46.898
[bright music]

05:50.211 --> 05:53.663
- [Jeff] Wanna guess
why I sprung you early?

05:53.698 --> 05:55.009
- What?

05:55.044 --> 05:56.873
- Can you take your?

05:56.908 --> 05:58.530
Can you turn your
music off please?

05:58.565 --> 06:01.119
[bright music]

06:03.880 --> 06:06.055
Got about a quarter tank.

06:06.089 --> 06:08.022
I'm gonna pull over.

06:08.057 --> 06:09.921
[bright music]

06:09.955 --> 06:12.579
Oh hey, they have meat sticks.

06:12.613 --> 06:13.545
I wonder if they have bison.

06:13.580 --> 06:14.408
- Gummies.

06:15.409 --> 06:16.514
- You hate gummy worms.

06:16.548 --> 06:19.137
[bright music]

06:27.076 --> 06:28.940
- [News Anchor] Search
continues for four inmates

06:28.974 --> 06:31.045
who escaped federal
custody this morning,

06:31.080 --> 06:33.876
killing two armed guards
and an inmate as they fled.

06:33.910 --> 06:37.535
Authorities say the men are
armed and extremely dangerous.

06:37.569 --> 06:38.398
In other news.

06:38.432 --> 06:40.952
[bright music]

06:45.577 --> 06:48.580
[women laughing]
[bright music]

06:48.615 --> 06:50.237
[bell ringing]
[register clanking]

06:50.271 --> 06:51.894
[bright music]

06:51.928 --> 06:52.964
Looks like the
Atlanta Braves are off

06:52.998 --> 06:54.793
to a great start this season.

06:54.828 --> 06:56.416
I'm gonna turn it over to Matt.

06:56.450 --> 06:59.073
[bright music]
[kids laughing]

06:59.108 --> 07:04.009
[bell ringing]
[bright music]

07:04.631 --> 07:05.977
- A small one.

07:06.011 --> 07:06.978
What flavor?

07:07.012 --> 07:11.845
[bright music]
[bell ringing]

07:30.035 --> 07:32.762
- [Becky] Can you picture?

07:32.797 --> 07:34.143
- Those are the shoes I have.

07:34.177 --> 07:34.971
Still looks good?

07:35.006 --> 07:35.972
- Yes.

07:36.007 --> 07:36.766
- Okay.
- Of course, of course.

07:36.801 --> 07:37.664
Yes, okay.

07:37.698 --> 07:38.492
Here we go.

07:38.527 --> 07:39.355
Ready?

07:39.389 --> 07:40.183
- Mm hm.

07:40.218 --> 07:41.012
- [Becky] Oh.

07:41.046 --> 07:42.807
I'm sorry, I'm sorry.

07:45.050 --> 07:47.156
Mom is in
serious painter mode.

07:49.158 --> 07:51.022
- What do you think?

07:51.056 --> 07:54.646
- [Becky] Why is Dora's
head way bigger than Dad's?

07:54.681 --> 07:56.614
- She's just so full
of herself, right.

07:56.648 --> 07:59.306
- [Becky] She is pretty awesome.

07:59.340 --> 08:00.963
Okay, got a surprise for you.

08:00.997 --> 08:02.309
Gotta close your eyes.

08:02.343 --> 08:05.001
[gentle music]

08:08.177 --> 08:09.040
There.

08:09.074 --> 08:10.351
Okay, open 'em.

08:11.870 --> 08:12.871
- Oh, Becky.

08:14.079 --> 08:15.564
Much love, girlie.

08:36.861 --> 08:38.414
- This whole thing.

08:40.035 --> 08:41.866
I know it's been hard,

08:43.212 --> 08:45.939
but you can't stay
angry forever.

09:00.781 --> 09:02.680
- Why would you bring me here?

09:02.714 --> 09:03.715
- Calm down, Chipmunk.

09:03.750 --> 09:05.752
- Don't call me that.

09:05.786 --> 09:07.547
I thought you said
it would take time.

09:07.581 --> 09:10.411
Like with the
realtors or whatever.

09:10.446 --> 09:12.552
- Yeah, so about that now.

09:12.586 --> 09:14.277
[energetic music]

09:14.312 --> 09:15.934
Can you turn that off, please?

09:15.969 --> 09:18.212
[energetic music]

09:18.247 --> 09:19.041
Now.

09:19.075 --> 09:20.698
[upbeat music]

09:20.732 --> 09:21.561
Off.

09:21.595 --> 09:23.942
[bright music]

09:23.977 --> 09:24.771
Becky.

09:24.805 --> 09:26.876
[upbeat music]

09:26.911 --> 09:28.429
Rebecca Hooper, if the
next button you press

09:28.464 --> 09:30.949
is not the off button, you're
grounded for two weeks.

