♪ Just know when the room
go cold I'm a ghost ♪

10:36.808 --> 10:38.776
- She wouldn't
want us to sell it.

10:38.810 --> 10:39.984
- [Jeff] Becky--

10:40.018 --> 10:40.812
- No, just because
she's not here anymore--

10:40.847 --> 10:42.503
- We're not selling it.

10:44.505 --> 10:46.128
Been trying to tell you.

10:46.162 --> 10:46.956
I changed my mind.

10:46.991 --> 10:48.337
We're keeping it.

10:51.340 --> 10:55.068
Oh, you forgot you hated
me for a minute, huh?

10:56.517 --> 10:57.795
- [Becky] Diego,
we're keeping it.

10:57.829 --> 10:58.692
We're keeping it.

10:58.727 --> 10:59.693
Come on.

10:59.728 --> 11:00.383
Come on, boy, let's go swimming.

11:00.418 --> 11:01.488
- No.

11:01.522 --> 11:02.696
- No, I wanna swim.

11:02.731 --> 11:04.180
- Yeah, but how
'bout after dinner?

11:04.215 --> 11:05.975
There's something else I
need to talk to you about.

11:06.010 --> 11:08.668
[horn beeping]

11:11.912 --> 11:13.500
- What is she doing here?

11:13.534 --> 11:14.812
- Well that's part of it.

11:14.846 --> 11:18.712
I invited Kayla and
Ty up for the weekend.

11:18.747 --> 11:19.713
You made it.

11:20.714 --> 11:22.371
- [Kayla] Thank you GPS.

11:22.405 --> 11:23.821
- I'll park it next to mine.

11:23.855 --> 11:25.339
- Do I have to tip the valet?

11:25.374 --> 11:26.168
- Yes.

11:26.202 --> 11:27.687
Yes, you do.

11:27.721 --> 11:28.688
- Oh, I missed you.

11:28.722 --> 11:30.690
- [Jeff] Same here.

11:30.724 --> 11:31.760
- Hey, Becky.

11:34.383 --> 11:35.833
It's so generous of
you to share your dad

11:35.867 --> 11:38.870
and this place with
us this weekend.

11:41.597 --> 11:44.600
The drive here was gorgeous.

11:44.634 --> 11:46.015
You didn't tell her that
we were coming, did you?

11:46.050 --> 11:47.189
- I tried.

11:47.223 --> 11:48.017
Hey, little man.

11:48.052 --> 11:49.363
How you doing?
- Hi.

11:49.398 --> 11:50.710
- I know someone who's
excited to meet you.

11:50.744 --> 11:52.090
[whistles] Come here.

11:52.125 --> 11:52.884
Oh.

11:52.919 --> 11:53.747
Oh, hi.

11:53.782 --> 11:55.093
- Oh, hi.

11:55.128 --> 11:56.750
- Oh, she's really nice.

11:56.785 --> 11:58.200
She's sweet.
- It's okay.

11:58.234 --> 12:00.858
- All right, girl,
give the man some room.

12:00.892 --> 12:01.582
- [Ty] What's her name?

12:01.617 --> 12:02.549
- Dora.

12:02.583 --> 12:04.033
Diego's down by the lake,

12:04.068 --> 12:05.863
but he takes a bit longer
getting used to new people,

12:05.897 --> 12:07.554
but he knows a lot of tricks.

12:07.588 --> 12:09.211
Pretty much anything Becky asks.

12:09.245 --> 12:11.903
Maybe she'll show
you if you ask.

12:11.938 --> 12:12.766
- Yeah.

12:12.801 --> 12:13.594
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

12:13.629 --> 12:14.423
- Yeah, oh see look.

12:14.457 --> 12:15.251
See, she likes you.

12:15.286 --> 12:17.081
- She likes everyone.

12:18.427 --> 12:19.877
- Why don't you go get Diego?

12:19.911 --> 12:21.879
'Cause we're about to eat.

12:21.913 --> 12:23.397
- Fine.

12:23.432 --> 12:25.054
- Will you take Ty with you?

12:25.089 --> 12:25.883
- What?

12:25.917 --> 12:26.746
No.

12:27.919 --> 12:29.576
- You let her walk all over you.

12:29.610 --> 12:30.473
- She's 13.

12:32.268 --> 12:33.580
Don't worry about Becky.

12:33.614 --> 12:36.238
She's like Diego,
takes a bit longer

12:36.272 --> 12:38.136
getting used to new people.

12:38.171 --> 12:40.069
Do you wanna help me
build the fire pit?

12:40.104 --> 12:42.278
We can have s'mores
after dinner.

12:42.313 --> 12:43.763
- What's s'mores?

12:45.350 --> 12:46.144
- What's s'mores?

12:46.179 --> 12:47.594
- I know.

12:47.628 --> 12:49.113
- Oh, you are in for a treat.

12:49.147 --> 12:49.976
Come on.

12:50.010 --> 12:52.979
[suspenseful music]

13:06.647 --> 13:07.614
- [Dominick] Good afternoon.

13:07.648 --> 13:09.823
- What's going on?

13:09.858 --> 13:10.997
- Could you step
out of the vehicle?

13:11.031 --> 13:14.034
[suspenseful music]

13:23.492 --> 13:24.355
We appreciate your compliance.

13:24.389 --> 13:25.943
You live nearby?

13:25.977 --> 13:27.807
- Half a mile that way.

13:27.841 --> 13:29.498
- Driver's license please.

13:29.532 --> 13:31.120
My partner's gonna
inspect your vehicle.

13:31.155 --> 13:34.158
[suspenseful music]

13:43.167 --> 13:45.721
Gunshot will carry half a mile.

13:45.755 --> 13:47.654
Don't wanna alarm your wife.

13:47.688 --> 13:48.828
- What?

13:48.862 --> 13:53.522
[suspenseful music]
[kids screaming]

13:54.868 --> 13:57.181
[soft music]

14:35.598 --> 14:37.877
[dog barking]

14:37.911 --> 14:40.396
[soft music]

15:06.457 --> 15:07.596
- [Kayla] Ty.

15:09.667 --> 15:12.118
Stop feeding the dog your food.

15:12.152 --> 15:13.050
- [Ty] But she's hungry.

15:13.084 --> 15:13.913
- No.

15:15.673 --> 15:18.158
[dog barking]

15:22.611 --> 15:25.269
- Becky, we've got
something that we would like

15:25.303 --> 15:27.098
to talk to you about.

15:28.962 --> 15:31.447
Can you look at me, Chipmunk?

15:32.621 --> 15:35.486
- I told you not
to call me that.

15:35.520 --> 15:38.938
- Yes Rebecca, I would
like to tell you something

15:38.972 --> 15:41.871
and I would like
you to look at me.

15:43.804 --> 15:44.633
Okay so.

15:46.117 --> 15:49.810
I know things have been
tough this past year.

15:51.157 --> 15:54.160
On all of us, but
especially on you.

15:55.989 --> 15:58.543
Still, we have to look forward.

16:01.132 --> 16:04.480
Part of the healing
process is moving on.

16:05.861 --> 16:09.830
Now, Kayla and I, we love
each other very much.

16:13.489 --> 16:16.147
So we've decided to get married.

16:19.702 --> 16:20.531
- What?

16:21.842 --> 16:24.328
- I know it's a big deal

16:24.362 --> 16:27.365
and it's gonna take
some getting used to,

16:27.400 --> 16:30.127
but it's what we want and--

16:30.161 --> 16:31.507
- Is this a joke?

16:31.542 --> 16:32.370
- It's.

16:33.509 --> 16:35.166
I think a more
stable environment

16:35.201 --> 16:37.686
will be a good thing for you.

16:46.246 --> 16:47.385
- [Becky] She
would've hated you.

16:47.420 --> 16:48.214
- Becky.

16:48.248 --> 16:50.768
[dog barking]

16:54.703 --> 16:55.497
Sorry.

16:55.531 --> 16:56.670
- That's okay.

16:56.705 --> 16:59.190
We both knew that this
wasn't going to be easy.

16:59.225 --> 17:00.053
I'm gonna go check on her.

17:00.088 --> 17:01.365
- No, I got it.

17:18.898 --> 17:20.211
- How could you?

17:25.630 --> 17:27.907
- I loved your mom so much.

17:27.943 --> 17:29.531
- Yeah.

17:29.565 --> 17:31.740
Yeah, I can really tell.

17:31.774 --> 17:32.568
- [Jeff] Becky.

17:32.603 --> 17:33.880
- [Becky] Diego.

17:33.914 --> 17:37.056
- Will you please come
back and talk, please?

17:37.090 --> 17:37.918
Becky.

17:47.928 --> 17:50.655
[dramatic music]

18:12.781 --> 18:14.300
- Ty, stop that.

18:14.334 --> 18:16.129
That's for you to eat.

18:16.164 --> 18:17.751
- Where did they go?

18:17.786 --> 18:19.098
- They're outside talking.

18:19.132 --> 18:19.926
They'll be right back.

18:19.960 --> 18:20.754
It's okay.

18:20.789 --> 18:23.102
[doorbell ringing]

18:23.136 --> 18:24.931
[soft music]

18:24.965 --> 18:26.588
Eat your dinner.

18:26.622 --> 18:28.969
[soft music]

18:33.284 --> 18:34.941
[doorbell ringing]

18:34.975 --> 18:36.253
[soft music]

18:36.287 --> 18:37.771
- Diego, we're staying.

18:37.806 --> 18:38.945
We're staying.

18:38.979 --> 18:39.773
Come on.

18:39.808 --> 18:40.602
Come on.

18:40.636 --> 18:43.122
[soft music]

18:47.678 --> 18:51.337
[doorbell ringing]

18:51.371 --> 18:53.270
- [Kayla] Hello, may I help you?

18:53.304 --> 18:55.651
[soft music]

19:06.006 --> 19:08.664
[girl grunting]

19:16.016 --> 19:18.157
[dog barking]

19:18.191 --> 19:20.814
[dog whining]

19:20.849 --> 19:23.334
[gentle music]

19:29.029 --> 19:33.033
- [Mother] Just play a little
bit of my favorite song.

19:33.068 --> 19:33.862
- Okay.

19:33.896 --> 19:36.520
[gentle music]

19:37.555 --> 19:40.179
[bright music]

19:42.042 --> 19:45.736
♪ I will stay by your side

19:45.770 --> 19:49.533
♪ I will stay by your side

19:49.567 --> 19:53.399
♪ And I want you to find me

19:53.433 --> 19:58.438
♪ So I'll stay by your side

19:59.370 --> 20:02.511
♪ I will stay by your side

20:02.546 --> 20:03.857
♪ I will

20:03.892 --> 20:04.686
- It's okay.

20:04.720 --> 20:07.516
[woman coughing]

20:07.551 --> 20:10.070
[dog whining]

20:35.751 --> 20:38.064
- Where's your mom, Ty?

20:38.098 --> 20:38.823
Kayla?

20:42.310 --> 20:44.070
- [Kayla] Jeff, this
gentleman lost his dog.

20:44.104 --> 20:46.900
- Yeah, I'm afraid he's
a bit of a Houdini.

20:46.935 --> 20:48.247
I'm sorry to
interrupt your dinner.

20:48.281 --> 20:49.282
It's nice to meet you, Jeff.

20:49.317 --> 20:51.077
- [Jeff] Hi.

20:51.111 --> 20:52.285
- [Kayla] Can I
get you some water?

20:52.320 --> 20:53.113
- Oh, that'd be great.

20:53.148 --> 20:54.080
Thank you.

20:54.114 --> 20:56.600
[eerie music]

21:03.676 --> 21:06.265
[gentle music]

21:18.656 --> 21:21.141
[soft music]

21:43.163 --> 21:46.166
[suspenseful music]

21:50.826 --> 21:52.656
- [Kayla] Here you go.

21:53.829 --> 21:57.005
- [Jeff] What kind
of dog did you say?

21:59.352 --> 22:00.180
- I didn't.

22:01.561 --> 22:05.324
- [Jeff] Well it might help to
know what we're looking for.

22:05.358 --> 22:08.327
[suspenseful music]

22:09.535 --> 22:11.226
Okay, well if there's
nothing else--

22:11.260 --> 22:13.055
- Cane Corso.

22:13.090 --> 22:15.230
- [Jeff] Your dog's a Corso?

22:15.264 --> 22:16.818
- No, your dog's a Corso.

22:16.852 --> 22:17.991
- [Jeff] Yes.

22:18.026 --> 22:19.648
- Doesn't look pure, though.

22:19.683 --> 22:20.477
- [Jeff] Well, we're not sure.

22:20.511 --> 22:21.719
She's a rescue.

22:21.754 --> 22:22.651
Why don't you give
us your number?

22:22.686 --> 22:24.170
- My dog is a rottweiler.

22:24.204 --> 22:25.654
Pure bred.

22:25.689 --> 22:29.348
Or as the Germans call them
[speaks in foreign language].

22:29.382 --> 22:30.521
Butcher's dog.

22:32.281 --> 22:33.524
Endurance.

22:33.559 --> 22:34.836
Intelligence.

22:34.870 --> 22:35.733
Strength.

22:35.768 --> 22:36.527
Traits they were bred for.

22:36.562 --> 22:37.839
It's in their blood.

22:37.873 --> 22:40.669
[soft music]

22:40.704 --> 22:42.706
That's why you never let
them mate with other breeds.

22:42.740 --> 22:44.017
You get the worst of both.

22:44.052 --> 22:46.192
- Okay, I think it's
time for you to go.

22:46.226 --> 22:47.055
I'm gonna go check on Ty.

22:47.089 --> 22:48.677
- You're leaving right now.

22:48.712 --> 22:51.922
[suspenseful music]

22:51.956 --> 22:52.750
- Clear out front.

22:52.785 --> 22:53.579
- Dining room.

22:53.613 --> 22:56.098
[suspenseful music]

22:56.133 --> 22:57.272
She's probably
going for a phone.

22:57.306 --> 23:00.275
[suspenseful music]

23:04.624 --> 23:06.039
Stay calm.

23:06.074 --> 23:07.869
Why don't you take
a seat on the couch?

